All Implemented Interfaces:
com.esotericsoftware.kryo.KryoSerializable, com.telenav.kivakit.kernel.interfaces.lifecycle.Initializable, com.telenav.kivakit.kernel.interfaces.naming.NamedObject, com.telenav.kivakit.kernel.interfaces.numeric.Countable, com.telenav.kivakit.kernel.interfaces.numeric.Sized, com.telenav.kivakit.kernel.language.collections.CompressibleCollection, PackedPrimitiveArray
public class BigSplitPackedArray extends PrimitiveSplitArray implements PackedPrimitiveArray
BigSplitPackedArray maintains an array of packed arrays, indexing them as a single larger array. The purpose in this is to avoid resizing as a very large packed array grows. Instead, when a write index is greater than the size of the BigSplitPackedArray, a new PackedArray is allocated and added to the list. This design is similar to the "rope" pattern for handling very large strings.
Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
